-- Germany's Schaeuble says EU finmins have issues with Hypo haircut
-- By Ilona Wissenbach
-- Fri Jul 11, 2014 01:39PM EDT
-- None



FREIBURG, Germany, July 11 (Reuters) - German Finance Minister Wolfgang Schaeuble said on Friday that EU finance ministers had problems with Austria's decision to write down debt owned by Hypo Alpe Adria [HAABI.UL].

"We all have significant problems with it - I've also told my Austrian colleague that," Schaeuble said at an event hosted by the Centre for European Policy in southwestern Germany.